      • treeStructureChanged

        public void treeStructureChanged(java.lang.Object source,
                        java.lang.Object[] path)
        Notifies the listeners that the structure of the tree has changed. In it's current implementation, this method is just a wrapper for the protected method fireTreeStructureChanged where the child index array and the children array are left empty. Wouter: be careful with calling this, The GUI below the source point will be collapsed
        Parameters:
        source - the source that triggered the change.
        path - a TreePath object that identifies the path to the parent of the modified item(s)
